Package com.SCHSRobotics.HAL9001.util.exceptions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExceptionChecker
    An class used to easily throw exceptions when a condition is met or not met.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ChannelDoesNotExistException
    An exception thrown if a channel in a color image does not exist.
    DumpsterFireException
    An exception thrown if something really bad happens.
    GuiNotPresentException
    An exception thrown if a GUI is needed, but is not present.
    HALConfigException
    An exception thrown when there is a problem with HAL's config system.
    HALGUIException
    An exception thrown when there is a problem with HAL's GUI system.
    HALMathException
    An exception thrown when there is a general problem with something that was attempted in a HAL math utility.
    InvalidLinkException
    An exception thrown if an invalid link is used in the LinkTo annotation.
    InvalidMoveCommandException
    An exception thrown if a drive train is given an invalid movement command.
    NotAnAlchemistException
    An exception that is thrown when things cannot be converted into other things or made out of nothing.
    NotARealGamepadException
    An exception that is thrown when someone tries to use an invalid gamepad to control the robot.
    NotBooleanInputException
    An exception thrown when a button meant to return boolean data is mapped to a button that does not return boolean data.
    NotDoubleInputException
    An exception thrown when a button meant to return double data is mapped to a button that does not return double data.
    NothingToSeeHereException
    An exception thrown if something needed is missing.
    NotVectorInputException
    An exception that is thrown when a button meant to return vector data is mapped to a button that does not return vector data.
    OpModeAnnotationNotPresentException
    An exception thrown if an @TeleOp or @Autonomous annotation is missing from an opmode being processed.
